\subsubsection{Fricatives}
\label{sec:fricative}

Chakali has five fricatives: /{\sls f}/, /{\sls v}/, /{\sls s}/, and /{\sls 
z}/. 
They  are distinguished by their phonation: /{\sls f}/ and  /{\sls s}/ are 
voiceless whereas /{\sls v}/ and /{\sls z}/ are voiced. 

